snippet.textDisplay: The 'Ring will never cease to exist. It's an amazing piece of work and for a century, it's totally fucking amazing to be there, even once. I've been there 2x while visiting Europe and it's superbly amazing to hit Caurosel at 120kph and feel one of your the right side of your car cocking up in the air and its the ONLY track where you could even drive a god damn lawnmower on if you just stick a plate on it. It's not rare to see trucks slamming on the track against faster machines like Porsches and Renaults.
